For topic [here](/Me.ZeroNetwork.bit/?Post/1BLueGvui1GdbtsjcKqCf4F67uKfritG49/1PniNzyi8fygvwyBaLpA9oBDVWZ5fXuJUw/1495610689) and [here](/Talk.ZeroNetwork.bit/?Topic:2_1PniNzyi8fygvwyBaLpA9oBDVWZ5fXuJUw/Dear+Chinese+friends), guess it may be nice to have a language sorting function for ZeroTalk.

I prefer to leave the main forum multi-lingual, then setup sub-forum for different language. So the language sorting function will be like:

1.  Article posted in sub-forum will be tagged with that language (also it will be displayed in the main forum).
2.  User who posts article in main forum will be suggested to add a language tag or choose it from list.
3.  User who doesn't add a language tag will be auto-sorted with script.
4.  Limit Unicode Range usage in sub-forum, to prevent user from posting with other language.*

From [Wikipedia: UTF-8](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UTF-8)
The UTF-8 code catagory for different language is basically like:

| Size | Unicode Range | Character Name | Relative Languages or States |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1-byte | U+0000..U+007F | ASCII (Hindu–Arabic numerals, Latin...) | English |
| 2-byte | U+0080..U+00FF | Latin-1 | Major: French, German, Spanish, Icelandic, Vietnamese |
| ... | U+0100..U+036F | *Latin Extended, etc. | ... |
| ... | U+0370..U+03FF | Greek and Coptic | Greek |
| ... | U+0400..U+04FF | Cyrillic | Major: Russian, Belorussian, Bulgarian, Abkhasian, Serbian |
| ... | U+0500..U+052F | *Cyrillic Supplement | ... |
| ... | U+0530..U+058F | *Armenian | Armenian |
| ... | U+0590..U+05FF | Hebrew | Hebrew |
| ... | U+0600..U+06FF | Arabic | Arabic |
| ... | U+0700..U+074F | *Syriac | ... |
| ... | U+0750..U+077F | *Arabic Supplement | Pakistan, Africa, old Persian, etc |
| ... | U+0780..U+07BF | *Thaana | Maldives |
| ... | U+07C0..U+07FF | *NKo | West Africa |
| 3-byte | U+0800..U+3040 | *Indic, Latin Extended, etc. | ... |
| ... | U+3041..U+30FF | Kana | Japanese, Okinawan, Ainu, Palauan |
| ... | U+3100..U+4DFF | *Hangul Compatibility Jamo, Enclosed CJK Letters and Months, etc. | ... |
| ... | U+4E00..U+9FFF | CJK Unified Ideographs | China, Hong Kong, Japan, North Korea, South Korea, Taiwan, Vietnam |
| ... | U+A000..U+ABFF | *Asian, Hangul Jamo Extended, etc. | ... |
| ... | U+AC00..U+D7AF | Hangul Syllables | Korean |
| ... | U+D7B0..U+FFFF | *Hangul Jamo Extended, Private Use Area, etc. | ... |
| 4-byte | U+10000..U+10FFFF | *Emoji, Smiley, Language from other planet, etc. | ... |

So the script will be like:

```
if (the_text.match(/[\u0370-\u03FF]/) {
  console.log('It\'s Greek');
  // Sort it to...
} else if (the_text.match(/[\u0400-\u04FF]/) {
  console.log('It\'s Cyrillic');
  // Sort it to...
} else if (the_text.match(/[\u0590-\u05FF]/) {
  console.log('It\'s Hebrew');
  // Sort it to...
} else if (the_text.match(/[\u0600-\u06FF]/) {
  console.log('It\'s Arabic');
  // Sort it to...
} else if (the_text.match(/[\u3041-\u30FF]/) {
  console.log('It\'s Kana');
  // Sort it to...
} else if (the_text.match(/[\uAC00-\uD7AF]/) {
  console.log('It\'s Hangul');
  // Sort it to...
} else if (the_text.match(/[\u4E00-\u9FFF]/) {
  console.log('It\'s CJK Unified Ideographs');
  // Sort it to...
} else {
  console.log('It\'s likely latin.');
  // Sort it to...
}
```

PS: Python has a library named [langid](https://github.com/saffsd/langid.py) that can be used to detect many languages. Dream tool to sort languages!

Reference:
[List of Unicode characters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Unicode_characters)
[Latin script in Unicode](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latin_script_in_Unicode)
[List of language families](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_language_families)

\* Added in 30/05/17
